{"title":"Moving from San Francisco to Austin: Complete Relocation Guide [2026]","description":"Compare cost of living, housing, taxes, and quality of life when moving from San Francisco to Austin. Data-driven relocation guide with calculators.","url":"https://urcity.com/compare/moving-from-sf-to-austin/","content":"\u003ch2 id=\"introduction\"\u003eIntroduction\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSan Francisco to Austin is one of the most popular relocation routes in America. Tech workers fleeing sky-high Bay Area costs find Austin offers a comparable tech scene at a fraction of the price.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"cost-of-living-comparison\"\u003eCost of Living Comparison\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eCategory\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSan Francisco\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eAustin\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSavings\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eOverall Index\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e269.3\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e119.3\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e-56%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eRent (1BR)\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$3,200/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$1,650/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e-$1,550/mo\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHome Price\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$1,200,000\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$450,000\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e-63%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eUtilities\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$160/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$140/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-13%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eGroceries\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$600/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$380/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-37%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eTransportation\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$200/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$150/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-25%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHealthcare\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$500/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$350/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-30%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMonthly savings potential: $2,000–$3,000\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"salary-calculator\"\u003eSalary Calculator\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you make \u003cstrong\u003e$150,000 in San Francisco\u003c/strong\u003e, you need approximately \u003cstrong\u003e$66,000 in Austin\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain the same standard of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"calculator-widget\" id=\"salary-calc\"\u003e\n  \u003ch3\u003eSalary Comparison Calculator\u003c/h3\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eCurrent Salary ($)\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cinput type=\"number\" id=\"current-salary\" value=\"150000\" min=\"0\" step=\"1000\"\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eFrom City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"from-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" \u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" selected\u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" \u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eTo City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"to-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" selected\u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" \u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" \u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cbutton class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"calculateSalary()\"\u003eCalculate\u003c/button\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-result\" id=\"salary-result\" style=\"display:none;\"\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eYou need \u003cstrong id=\"needed-salary\"\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e in \u003cspan id=\"target-city-name\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e to maintain the same standard of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cp id=\"salary-difference\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\nfunction calculateSalary() {\n  const salary = parseFloat(document.getElementById('current-salary').value);\n  const fromCity = document.getElementById('from-city').value;\n  const toCity = document.getElementById('to-city').value;\n  \n  const colIndex = {\n    'nyc': 187.2,\n    'sf': 269.3,\n    'la': 173.3,\n    'chicago': 110.8,\n    'austin-tx': 119.3\n  };\n  \n  const cityNames = {\n    'nyc': 'New York City',\n    'sf': 'San Francisco',\n    'la': 'Los Angeles',\n    'chicago': 'Chicago',\n    'austin-tx': 'Austin'\n  };\n  \n  const neededSalary = Math.round(salary * (colIndex[toCity] / colIndex[fromCity]));\n  const diff = salary - neededSalary;\n  \n  document.getElementById('needed-salary').textContent = '$' + neededSalary.toLocaleString();\n  document.getElementById('target-city-name').textContent = cityNames[toCity];\n  \n  const diffEl = document.getElementById('salary-difference');\n  if (diff \u003e 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would save \u003cstrong\u003e$' + diff.toLocaleString() + '/year\u003c/strong\u003e by moving.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-positive';\n  } else if (diff \u003c 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would need \u003cstrong\u003e$' + Math.abs(diff).toLocaleString() + '/year more\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain your lifestyle.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-negative';\n  } else {\n    diffEl.textContent = 'Cost of living is roughly the same.';\n  }\n  \n  document.getElementById('salary-result').style.display = 'block';\n}\n\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"housing-market\"\u003eHousing Market\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"san-francisco\"\u003eSan Francisco\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian home: $1,200,000\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian rent (1BR): $3,200/month\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrice per sq ft: $1,100\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"austin\"\u003eAustin\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian home: $450,000\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian rent (1BR): $1,650/month\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrice per sq ft: $285\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYou can buy a 4-bedroom house in Austin for less than a 1-bedroom condo in San Francisco.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"taxes\"\u003eTaxes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eTax Type\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSan Francisco\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eAustin\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eState Income Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e9.3%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e0%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eCity Income Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e0%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e0%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSales Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e8.625%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e8.25%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eProperty Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e~0.88%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e~1.8%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAnnual tax savings on $150K salary: ~$14,000\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"climate\"\u003eClimate\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSan Francisco\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eAustin\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSummer High\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e67°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e96°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eWinter Low\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e46°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e41°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSunny Days\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e259\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e228\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHumidity\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHigh\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrade-off:\u003c/strong\u003e Austin summers are hot (100°F+), but you\u0026rsquo;ll never need a jacket in July.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"culture--lifestyle\"\u003eCulture \u0026amp; Lifestyle\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-youll-miss-from-san-francisco\"\u003eWhat You\u0026rsquo;ll Miss from San Francisco\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWorld-class dining and Michelin stars\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProximity to Napa and Yosemite\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDense, walkable neighborhoods\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCool summer weather\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProgressive culture\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-youll-gain-in-austin\"\u003eWhat You\u0026rsquo;ll Gain in Austin\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLive music everywhere\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBBQ and Tex-Mex\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo state income tax\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMore space for your money\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFriendly, laid-back culture\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"best-neighborhoods-in-austin-for-sf-transplants\"\u003eBest Neighborhoods in Austin for SF Transplants\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEast Austin\u003c/strong\u003e — Trendy, artsy, most like the Mission District\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSouth Congress\u003c/strong\u003e — Walkable shops and restaurants, like Hayes Valley\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDowntown Austin\u003c/strong\u003e — High-rise living, like SOMA\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMueller\u003c/strong\u003e — Planned community, like Mission Bay\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"is-it-worth-it\"\u003eIs It Worth It?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYes — if you can handle the heat and driving.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe financial case is overwhelming: you\u0026rsquo;ll save $40,000+ annually on housing and taxes. Austin\u0026rsquo;s tech scene is robust (Apple, Google, Meta, Tesla all have major presence). The main trade-offs are public transit (minimal) and summer heat (extreme).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDisclaimer:\u003c/strong\u003e All cost of living figures, housing prices, tax estimates, and savings calculations on this page are provided for informational purposes only and do not constitute financial, legal, tax, or real estate advice. Actual costs and savings will vary based on your specific circumstances, lifestyle, income, deductions, and local market conditions. URCity and Northshore Press are not financial advisors, tax professionals, or real estate agents. Always consult qualified professionals before making relocation or financial decisions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"frequently-asked-questions\"\u003eFrequently Asked Questions\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"will-my-salary-go-down\"\u003eWill my salary go down?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePossibly.\u003c/strong\u003e Tech salaries in Austin are typically 15–25% lower than SF. However, the cost savings more than offset the difference. Many remote workers keep their SF salary.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"is-austins-tech-scene-real\"\u003eIs Austin\u0026rsquo;s tech scene real?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYes.\u003c/strong\u003e The \u0026ldquo;Silicon Hills\u0026rdquo; nickname is deserved. Major employers include Apple (7,000+ employees), Google, Meta, Tesla, Dell, and thousands of startups.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"hows-the-food-scene\"\u003eHow\u0026rsquo;s the food scene?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcellent, different.\u003c/strong\u003e Austin is a BBQ and Tex-Mex town, not a fine dining city. But the food is incredible in its own way — Franklin Barbecue, Torchy\u0026rsquo;s Tacos, and food trucks everywhere.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"whats-the-biggest-culture-shock\"\u003eWhat\u0026rsquo;s the biggest culture shock?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe pace and the politics.\u003c/strong\u003e Austin is liberal by Texas standards but conservative by California standards. Everything moves slower. People are friendlier. There\u0026rsquo;s no ocean.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"data-sources\"\u003eData Sources\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCost of living: Council for Community and Economic Research (C2ER)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHousing data: Zillow Research\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTax data: Tax Foundation\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMigration data: IRS Statistics of Income\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLast updated: June 28, 2026\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n"}